President Barack Obama announced his intent to nominate several individuals for key administration posts. Ellen O. Tauscher, a seven-term member of Congress, was nominated for Under Secretary of State for Arms Control and International Security. Homer Lee Wilkes, a 28-year veteran of the Natural Resources and Conservation Service, was nominated for Under Secretary for Natural Resources and Environment at the Department of Agriculture. Carmen Nazario, an Assistant Professor at the Inter American University of Puerto Rico, was nominated for Assistant Secretary for Children and Families at the Department of Health and Human Services. Andrew J. Shapiro, a Senior Advisor to Secretary of State Hillary Rodham Clinton, was nominated for Assistant Secretary for Political-Military Affairs at the Department of State. Richard G. Newell, the Gendell Associate Professor of Energy and Environmental Economics at Duke University, was nominated for Administrator of the Energy Information Administration.